cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SY 

This paper is about deep reinforcement learning and its application to the Atari 2600 benchmark. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the Atari 2600 benchmark involves visual input. The paper also discusses the use of robotics in experiments, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.RO (Robotics) as well. Finally, the paper discusses the combination of different extensions to the DQN algorithm, which could also make it relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
